# CLI Architecture

## Main Components

The CLI crate ([crates/cli/](mdc:crates/cli/)) contains the main application logic:

- **[src/main.rs](mdc:crates/cli/src/main.rs)** - Binary entry point
- **[src/lib.rs](mdc:crates/cli/src/lib.rs)** - Library entry point
- **[src/cli.rs](mdc:crates/cli/src/cli.rs)** - CLI argument parsing and commands
- **[src/serve.rs](mdc:crates/cli/src/serve.rs)** - HTTP server implementation
- **[src/logging.rs](mdc:crates/cli/src/logging.rs)** - Logging configuration

## Server Architecture

- Uses Axum web framework for HTTP server
- Implements OpenAPI/Swagger documentation with `utoipa`
- Provides health check endpoints
- Supports both CLI and server modes

## Configuration

- Integrates with [faber-config](mdc:crates/config/) crate
- Loads configuration from [config/default.toml](mdc:config/default.toml)
- Supports environment variable overrides
- Validates configuration on startup

## Dependencies

Key dependencies from workspace [Cargo.toml](mdc:Cargo.toml):

- `axum` - Web framework
- `clap` - CLI argument parsing
- `tokio` - Async runtime
- `tracing` - Structured logging
- `serde_json` - JSON serialization
- `thiserror` - Error handling

## Development

- Run with `cargo run` for CLI mode
- Run with `cargo run -- serve` for server mode
- Use `make dev` for Docker development environment
- Health check available at `http://localhost:3000/health`
